    "We analyze the results through three approaches.",
    "First, we calculate Shannon's Diversity Index (H ′) a version of Shannon entropy based on the natural logarithm that is commonly used in ecological studies to measure diversity within a community:",
    "where R represents the total number of unique entities in the dataset (defined by the 2,693 reference entities), and p i is the proportion of the total population for entity i.",
    "We also calculate Pielou's Evenness Index (J ′), which normalizes Shannon's diversity index relative to a maximum possible H ′ that would occur if all entities were equally-well represented (Pielou 1966), corresponding to Definition 1 above.",
    "The results are reported in Table 3."
  ]
}